CPRF slogans favored
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Political parties and organizations of Peru on April 14 issued a joint statement supporting slogans of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland for great national unity and the reunification of the country to mark the 1st anniversary of the publication of General Secretary Kim Jong Il's famous work "Let Us Reunify the Country Independently and Peacefully through the Great Unity of the Entire Nation."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The statement said that the five-point policy of  great national unity laid down by Kim Jong Il is the banner of great unity and of reunification with which to closely unite all the Koreans into one.     It expressed conviction that under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il all the Korean people would achieve great unity and certainly reunify the country with the  support of the  progressives of the world.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It earnestly appealed to the progressive political parties and people of all social standings in all countries that have consistently supported the Korean people's cause of reunification to turn out in an international  solidarity movement for peace and independent reunification of the Korean peninsula in hearty response to the reunification slogans.

Greatest leader ever known in human  history
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Dilip Barua, general secretary of the central committee of the Communist Party of Bangladesh (Marxist-Leninist), who was in Korea to mark  Sun's Day had a press interview here at which he spoke highly of the  President Kim Il Sung.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said that while staying here  he looked up to Portraits of Kim Il Sung with a beam of smile in different parts of Pyongyang, which made him have deeper reverence for the President.   He continued:   Kim Il Sung will always be not only with the Korean people but also with the world progressives. This is my confidence that has already been  deeply rooted in my heart.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The President was the greatest leader ever known in human history. He devoted his all to the people's happiness as their leader.   He made the Korean people  an independent people who most value the national dignity, which is one of his great achievements. Thanks to his great services Korea became a country strongest in independence.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   But for the strong armed forces founded and led by the President, the Korean people could not defend what they have achieved in the revolution at the cost of blood nor the  sovereignty of the country.   The U.S. and its followers could inspect military installations and even the presidential palace of another sovereign country and intrude into its airspace at will. But that is not the same case with the DPRK at all. The will of the Korean armed forces and people not to tolerate any encroachment upon the sovereignty has been proved in practice.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The DPRK successfully solved the question of succession to the leadership. Kim Jong Il gives wise guidance over the work of  the party, the state and the army as a whole.
   It is a principle and stand always maintained by Kim Jong Il to do all work as the president did and work out all lines and policies as he intended. 
   Thanks to Kim Jong Il the history of Kim Il Sung still continues.
   Kim Il Sung is immortal as the sun that will throw its brilliant rays of Juche for all people forever.

Japan's misbehaviour under fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The delegate of the DPRK denounced the Japanese authorities for refusing to admit the past crimes of Japan, apologize and compensate for them and making desperate efforts to whitewash them.This denunciation came when discussions on human rights of women were under way at the 55th Meeting of the UN Commission  on Human Rights in Geneva on April 13.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The delegate said that outrages against Korean coeds in national costume, subversive activities and arson on Korean schools reminiscent of discrimination and atrocities Japan  committed against the Korean people in the past still continue in Japan.    These are attributable to the Japanese government's anachronistic policy towards the past crimes, the delegate said, and went on:   Japan should make a proper apology and take a step for deserved compensation for its crimes against humankind so as to liquidate the crime-woven past at an early date.

Part 46 of film "the Nation and Destiny" released
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The April 25 Film Studio of the Korean People's Army released part 46 of the multi-part feature film "the Nation and Destiny," which is the 2nd serial about Choe Hyon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  An anti-Japanese revolutionary fighter, Choe Hyon held a responsible post in the Korean People's Army.   This part deals with the hero's struggle in the enemy rear during the Fatherland Liberation War (June 1950-july 1953). It teaches through a truthful depiction the truth of the revolution that the destiny of the fatherland and the nation can be saved and defended only when everyone absolutely trusts and follows the great leader.   It also tells the people if they are not guided by a great leader and they fail to breathe the same with their leader, the revolution is bound to fail as their idea changes and the weapons in the hands of the revolutionaries  get rusty.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A preview of the film was held at the April 25 House of Culture on Saturday.
   Senior party and state officials appreciated the film.

Evening gala of servicemen 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The Ministry of the People's Armed Forces sponsored an evening gala at Ginseng Plaza on Saturday to celebrate the 67th foundation anniversary of the heroic Korean People's Army. Among those present there were KPA vice marshals, Jo Myong Rok, director of the general political department, Kim Yong Chun, chief of the general staff, and Kim Il Chol, Minister of the People's armed Forces.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In the gala the participants danced to the melodies of such songs as "We will remain loyal to the party's leadership," "Let's defend socialism" and "Let's support our Supreme Commander with arms."    In the course they demonstrated the will of the KPA officers and men to reliably defend socialism with arms, take the lead in making a breakthrough in the building of a prosperous and strong state and discharge their mission as the pillar of revolution.

KPA is invincible
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Invincible is the Korean People's Army (KPA), grown and gained in strength under the guidance of the three commanders of Mt. Paektu and trained through decisive battles of nearly 70 years against imperialism.   Rodong Sinmun today stresses this in an editorial dedicated to the 67th army day.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The KPA is invincible as it is the best in terms of loyalty to the party and the leader, revolutionary trait, war strategy and methods, and discipline and unity, the editorial says, and goes on:   The nearly 70 years of our revolutionary armed forces is a history of glorious revolutionary activities conducted by the three commanders of Mt. Paektu.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The great leader President Kim Il Sung long ago founded the immortal Juche idea and basing himself on it gave a clear exposition of all the problems arising in the army building in the present era.  Kim Jong Suk, a woman commander of Mt. Paektu, indicated the way of strengthening and turning the revolutionary army into an army of the leader.   The respected Marshal Kim Jong Il has made great contributions to developing and enriching the President's idea and theory on Juche-oriented army building in a comprehensive way.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He creatively advanced ideas and theories that serve as a guideline in building the revolutionary armed forces in our era. Among them are a soldiers-centred theory that successful army building is decided by servicemen, an idea of achieving unshakable unity between officers and men, between superiors and inferiors and between army and people, a theory of imbuing the whole army with the revolutionary idea of the leader and an idea of strictly ensuring the party's leadership over the army.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The spirit of devotedly defending the leader and the spirit of human bomb and suicidal attack, being displayed among KPA servicemen today, are an expression of their noble sense of obligation to repay the benevolence of the great Kim Jong Il who has trained and led them.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean revolutionary armed forces are greeting the heyday of their development under his leadership, the editorial points out, and further says:   The invincible might of our People's Army lies in that it is the most staunch army with invariable class stand and unwavering fidelity to revolutionary principle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The imperialists' "peace strategy" or "appeasement policy" can never work on our army.   Its might also lies in the fact that it is the incomparably brave army, grim in making resolution and merciless in striking.   It is the spirit of the KPA to decisively fight against arrogant attack of the imperialist aggressors and give merciless blows to them. Its striking ability is unlimited and there is no room on this planet to evade such strike.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The KPA is also invincible because the revolutionary military discipline of acting only under the order of the respected Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il has been strictly observed by the whole army.   The KPA officers and men are only committed to observing the principles of absolutely and unconditionally implementing orders and instructions of the Supreme Commander.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   More powerful than nuclear weapons is the might of our People's Army thinking and acting as one with high consciousness and awareness.
   Once the Supreme Commander issues an order, the KPA will go into action as one like a fierce tiger and mercilessly annihilate the enemy and thus achieve the cause of national reunification.

Wreaths and floral baskets presented on Army Day
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Senior party and state officials, officers and men of the People's Army and working people visited the Revolutionary Martyrs' Cemetery on Mt. Taesong, the Patriotic Martyrs' Cemetery and the monument to victory in the Fatherland Liberation War in Pyongyang to lay wreaths and floral baskets on Sunday on the occasion of the 67th founding anniversary of the Korean People's Army (KPA).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   General Secretary Kim Jong Il sent wreaths to be placed on the wreath-laying stands of the Revolutionary Martyrs' Cemetery on Mt. Taesong and the Patriotic Martyrs' Cemetery and a floral basket to be laid before the main sculpture "victory" of the monument to the victory in the Fatherland Liberation War.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Also seen there were wreaths and a floral basket in the joint name of the WPK Central Committee,  the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and the cabinet of the DPRK and wreaths and floral baskets in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, the Ministry of Public Security and working people's organizations.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Meanwhile, wreaths were laid before the statues of martyrs and the monuments to and tombs of the fallen fighters in various parts of the country.
